  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 23 g
  protein: 12 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1130 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve @Mini Cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons. Roughly
chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Place @Shelled Edamame{4%ounce} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until
tender, ~{45%seconds}. Drain any excess water if necessary. Transfer to a
#paper-towel-lined plate{} to cool. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Wipe out
bowl.

While edamame cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}
and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste (use less if you prefer less heat).

In bowl used for edamame, combine @Red Cabbage and Carrot Mix{4%ounce},
cucumber, @Sesame Dressing{1.5%ounce}, and half the cilantro.

Meanwhile, massage @Microwavable Rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains.
Partially open package and insert @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Microwave according to
package instructions, ~{90%seconds}. Fluff with a #fork{}.

> To make it easier to fluff the rice, transfer to a bowl first.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with edamame and salad in separate sections.
Drizzle soy-Sriracha mixture over everything; garnish with @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon}
and remaining cilantro. Serve.